She gets herself a glass of water and comes to sit on the other end of the sofa. Not close. Appropriately far.
<p>You talk – lightly, about nothing important. The show on TV. Whether the weather's turning. She has a dry sense of humor you hadn't quite noticed before.</p>
<p>Eventually she sets her glass down and stands. "I should sleep." She pauses in the doorway. "It's nice, though. Having someone around."</p>
<p>You're not sure exactly what she means by that.</p>
